cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.HC

The paper discusses the usage of bibliometrics in research evaluation, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely categories as they deal with bibliometrics and research evaluation. cs.CY (Computational Complexity) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are less likely but still possible as they may involve evaluating research output. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also a possibility as the paper discusses the cognitive and decision-making processes involved in using bibliometrics.
